==English==
===Etymology===
Old English [[on#Old English|on]] [[efn]] literally ‘on even’.  Cognate with German [[neben]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /ə'nɛnt/

===Preposition===
'''anent'''
# ''(obsolete)'' [[against]], in front of
# ''(archaic)'' [[concerning]], with regard to
#:*'''1922''': Mr Bloom and Stephen entered the cabman’s shelter, an unpretentious wooden structure, where, prior to then, he had rarely, if ever, been before; the former having previously whispered to the latter a few hints '''anent''' the keeper of it.  (Joyce, ''Ulysses'')